    "narrative": "For Ghost Ride the WHIP on this April 23rd, our lineup is anchored by the elite 87.14 projection for **Corbin Carroll**, who faces a favorable matchup against Martin. With a substantial 17% boost due to the opponent's pitching weakness and an additional 6% credit for hitting in the three-hole, **Corbin Carroll** is our primary offensive engine. We are also capitalizing on the high-upside environment provided by Waldron; both **Mickey Moniak** (75.75) and **Kyle Karros** (59.58) benefit immensely from this target, with **Mickey Moniak** specifically thriving due to a massive 14% park factor and a 19% SP skill advantage. Despite hitting lower in the order, **Jose Caballero** (64.17) remains a high-floor play today, buoyed by a 13% platoon advantage against Tolle, helping us chase the scarce stolen base category that drives our roster construction.\n\nThe decision to bench **Brice Turang** (45.53) was the most difficult call of the morning. While **Brice Turang** offers the elite sprint speed we covet, the 2.71 xERA of Skubal acts as an absolute anchor on his efficiency, effectively neutralizing his utility. Ultimately, the optimizer prioritized the aggressive matchups for **Giancarlo Stanton** and **Austin Riley** over the risk of starting **Brice Turang** against such a disciplined arm. We remain cautious regarding **James Wood** (53.19); despite his lead-off status providing a 10% boost, his encounter with Ritchie (2.57 xERA) presents a significant hurdle that keeps his score hovering near our marginal threshold. We are holding **Dalton Rushing**, **Alex Freeland**, and **Josh Naylor** in reserve today, as they failed to clear our 40.0 efficiency floor or were sidelined by scheduling, leaving the heavy lifting to our active starters against the weaker arms in today\u2019s slate.",
